Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:965):
`loadJobs()` can be triggered from multiple places (manual refresh, filter changes, tab activation, and the auto-refresh interval) without guarding against concurrent in-flight requests. If a slower request resolves after a newer one, it can overwrite `jobs`/`jobsNextCursor` with stale data and cause flicker. Consider skipping when `jobsLoading` is already true, or cancelling/ignoring prior requests (e.g., via AbortController/cancellation token or a request sequence id).
---
Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:410):
`providerList` uses `notificationProviders.value ?? health.value?.providers ?? []`, but `notificationProviders` is initialized via `useDataApi(..., { initialData: [] })`, so `notificationProviders.value` is never `null`/`undefined` (it will be `[]` even when the providers request fails). This means the health endpoint's `providers` list is effectively ignored, and the Health tab can incorrectly show no provider readiness. Consider falling back based on `providersError` or `.length` (e.g., use `notificationProviders.value?.length ? notificationProviders.value : (health.value?.providers ?? [])`).

